  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Shred half of the <strong>red gem lettuce<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely and chop the rest roughly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the wedges have been in the oven for 10 mins, add the <strong>chicken burger patties</strong> to a separate tray (use <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> to prevent them from sticking!) and put the tray in the oven for 12 min or until starting to brown</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken burgers have had 12 min, remove the tray from the oven and top them with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>brioche rolls</strong>, cut-side up, to the other side of the tray</p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 3 min or until the cheese has melted and the burgers are cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>melty chicken burgers</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, spread the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> on the top and bottom of the <strong>brioche rolls</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-bbq-chicken-burger-with-wedges/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Assemble the <strong>brioche rolls</strong> with a handful of finely <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>melty chicken burger</strong> and <strong>hickory smoked BBQ sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Serve the <strong>potato wedges</strong> and<strong> remaining shredded lettuce </strong>to the side</p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>lettuce</strong> with some<strong> olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
